{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"992271de-6cde-4973-bdb3-0ddd7c0450dc","content":"On macOS, the OS automatically generates **`.ips` crash reports** when a process crashes. You don't need `createdump`.\n\n**Where to find them:**\n\n- **`~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/`** — crash reports for your user\n- **`/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/`** — system-wide crash reports\n\nLook for a file named like `YourAppName_YYYY-MM-DD-HHMMSS_macOS.ips`.\n\n**Quick command to find recent reports:**\n\n```bash\nls -lt ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/*.ips | head -5\n```\n\nYou can also open **Console.app → Crash Reports** to browse them with a GUI.\n\n**To get a core dump** instead, run `ulimit -c unlimited` before launching your app — macOS will write a core file to `/cores/`.\n\nIf you need help **symbolicating** the `.ips` crash log to map native frames back to .NET runtime source, let me know — I have a skill for that.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dde5c3ac-ebec-4e2d-8d08-867254fa6930","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT .NET app on macOS, without `createdump`. This is a knowledge question — I don't need to search code or run commands. Let me answer directly.","outputTokens":322,"requestId":"DA04:388A0A:719A5C7:7A4014D:6A03D89F"},"id":"6bf07c14-d338-4f3a-9466-a1e724f0bc22","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:49:30.738Z","parentId":"b608680f-c5f8-4ec4-a4b0-ca575e146c50"}
